edu.sjsu.cs.cs151.checkers.model

Class Model

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.sjsu.cs.cs151.checkers.model.Model

  • public class Model
extends java.lang.Object
    Model maintains the game state of a single game of Checkers. It monitors Pieces, Checkers (tiles), and their positions on a board.
    Author:
    seanz

    • Method Detail

      • reset

        public void reset()
        reset() restores the game board to its initial state. By default, it constructs an 8x8 array of Checkers, and populates them with three rows of Pieces for each side.

      • selectChecker

        public boolean selectChecker(Position pos)
        selectChecker sets the origin and currentPiece private fields. origin currentPiece are used in other methods like movePiece.
        Parameters:
        pos - - a user selected Position
        Returns:
        true - if a valid piece was selected, false otherwise

      • determineValidMoves

        public Position[] determineValidMoves()
        determineValidMoves decides which Positions around the origin and currentPiece contain Checkers that can be safely moved to.
        Returns:
        Position[] validMoves - an array of Positions that correspond to valid Checkers. 0, 2, 4, and 6 correspond to single-space moves. 1, 3, 5, and 7 are jump moves, going from lower left, to lower right, to upper left, to upper right.

      • movePiece

        public boolean movePiece(Position dest)
        movePiece moves a piece from one Position and Checker to another user-specified one. If the selected destination is invalid, movePiece will simply return.
        Parameters:
        dest - - the user-selected destination Position.

      • jump

        public void jump(int whichMove,
                 Position dest)
        jump() moves a piece by two spaces and jumps over an opponent piece, removing it from play. It is called exclusively by movePiece in the event that a destination Position requires a jump.
        Parameters:
        whichMove - - an int, 1-4, that determines the direction that the piece will jump. 1 = lower left, 2 = lower right, 3 = upper left, 4 = upper right
        dest - - the destination Position

      • deselect

        public void deselect()
        deselect sets the origin and currentPiece fields to null, resetting them.

      • switchTurn

        public void switchTurn()
        switchTurn alters the game state by switching the color currently in play.

      • checkWinCondition

        public Piece.Color checkWinCondition()
        checkWinCondition checks to see if either color has won by eliminating all opponent pieces. It sets either blackWon or redWon to true if the opposing remaining__Pieces == 0.

      • getInstance

        public static Model getInstance()
        getInstance returns the static instance of Model. (Singleton Pattern)
        Returns:
        instance - the instance of Model

      • getBoard

        public Checker[][] getBoard()
        getBoard returns board, a private field.
        Returns:
        board - a 2d Checker array

      • getOrigin

        public Position getOrigin()
        getOrigin returns origin, a private field representing a currently selected position on the board.
        Returns:
        origin - a Position representing the current selected position

      • getLastOrigin

        public Position getLastOrigin()
        getLastOrigin returns lastOrigin, a private field representing the previously selected position on the board.
        Returns:
        lastOrigin - a Position representing the previously selected position

      • canJumpAgain

        public boolean canJumpAgain()
        canJumpAgain returns whether a piece that has just previously jumped has remaining jump moves.
        Returns:
        canJumpAgain - whether the currentPiece has any valid jump moves

      • getCurrentColor

        public Piece.Color getCurrentColor()
        getCurrentColor returns currentColor, a private field representing the current player's turn/color.
        Returns:
        currentColor - Color.RED or Color.BLACK, depending on whose turn it is

      • getCurrentPiece

        public Piece getCurrentPiece()
        getCurrentPiece returns currentPiece, a private field representing the currently selected Piece.
        Returns:
        currentPiece - the currently selected Piece, corresponding to the currently selected Position
